pokedexEntries.red: A team of Diglett triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.
pokedexEntries.blue: A team of Diglett triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.
pokedexEntries.yellow: A team of triplets that can burrow over 60 MPH. Due to this, some people think it's an earthquake.
pokedexEntries.gold: Its three heads bob separately up and down to loosen the soil nearby, making it easier for it to burrow.
pokedexEntries.silver: Extremely powerful, they can dig through even the hardest ground to a depth of over 60 miles.
pokedexEntries.crystal: These Diglett triplets dig over 60 miles below sea level. No one knows what it's like underground.
pokedexEntries.ruby: Dugtrio are actually triplets that emerged from one body. As a result, each triplet thinks exactly like the other two triplets. They work cooperatively to burrow endlessly.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: Dugtrio are actually triplets that emerged from one body. As a result, each triplet thinks exactly like the other two triplets. They work cooperatively to burrow endlessly.
pokedexEntries.emerald: Because the triplets originally split from one body, they think exactly alike. They work cooperatively to burrow endlessly through the ground.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: In battle, it digs through the ground and strikes the unsuspecting foe from an unexpected direction.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: A team of Diglett triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.
pokedexEntries.diamond: Its three heads move alternately, driving it through tough soil to depths of over 60 miles.

pokedexEntries.omegaRuby: Dugtrio are actually triplets that emerged from one body. As a result, each triplet thinks exactly like the other two triplets. They work cooperatively to burrow endlessly.
pokedexEntries.alphaSapphire: Dugtrio are actually triplets that emerged from one body. As a result, each triplet thinks exactly like the other two triplets. They work cooperatively to burrow endlessly.
pokedexEntries.sun: This set of triplets moves cooperatively. It's the power of teamwork that enables this Pokémon to dig to a depth of 60 miles.
pokedexEntries.moon: Despite the closeness between this Pokémon and farmers and other people, no one has ever seen the parts of it concealed underground.
pokedexEntries.ultraSun: While the three of them normally get along splendidly, on rare occasions a huge fight will break out over which head gets to eat first.
pokedexEntries.ultraMoon: Dugtrio’s heads are sleek and smooth and incredibly hard. It can dig through any soil with its headbutts.
